main event: Numerous luminous objects appeared in the sky over Lubbock, Texas, moving rapidly in a generally northeasterly direction.
interesting points: The objects appeared suddenly as a group, passed over the observers, then disappeared after a total elapsed time of 12-15 seconds.
The objects were observed by several persons, appeared to be about 1/2 to 1 degree in size, and were bright enough to light up the surrounding terrain.
The movement of the objects appeared to be smooth and regular, without erratic motion.
Several other sightings were reported in the same general area and time period.
The report includes multiple photographs of the unidentified objects in flight over Lubbock, Texas.
sighted object: numerous luminous objects in the sky
witnesses: 2/Lt. D. C. Barker, A.C. and other witnesses
photographs: yes, the report includes 8 photographs of the unidentified objects
